klanddavid h wassermandirector david h wassermandirector restonbenjamin g wolffpresident and ceo kirklanddavid zufallsvp  network systems reston commissioner h brian thompson select page h brian thompson commissioner h brian thompson as first a pioneer and now as a veteran senior executive has had decades of disproportionate influence on the competitive landscape of the global communications industry he currently serves as executive chairman of gtt as a member of the irish prime minister’s irelandamerica economic advisory board commissioner thompson served as chairman of comsat international which was the largest independent telecommunications operator serving all of latin america and which was eventually absorbed by british telecom he served as chairman and ceo of global telesystems group inc lci international and vice chairman of the board of qwest previously he served as executive vice president of mci communications corporation contributing to the company’s growth from  million to  billion in revenue and guiding the internationalization of the business previously commissioner thompson was a management consultant with mckinsey  company where he specialized in the management of telecommunications and technology enterprises he currently serves on the boards as a director of pendrell corporation penske automotive group and sonus networks inc and formerly served on the boards of arraycomm axcelis technologies inc bell canada international inc comcast uk cable partners limited dyncorp williams communications group inc and golden books commissioner thompson served as chairman of both the advisory committee for telecommunications and more recently the advisory committee on infocoms he served as chairman of telecom eireann ireland’s incumbent telephone company he is a member of the board of trustees of the lab school of washington  baltimore and is a former chairman of the us competitive telecommunications association he also served on the university of massachusetts chancellor’s executive committee and as a trustee of capitol college commissioner thompson continues to head his own private equity investment and advisory firm universal telecommunications inc which focuses on both startup companies and consolidations taking place in the information and telecommunications business areas thompson is a giic chairman emeritus and in this role had a major influence on information infrastructure investment and the rise of competitive telecommunications throughout the world giic citation the giic cites brian thompson for his impressive leadership credentials in the international telecommunications arena for his influence in global information infrastructure competition policy across a wide array of high consequence issues and for his impact on emerging industry executives through his availability to share his extensive insights by the numbers st ceo to serve as company spokesman in tv commercials  sectors bridged through innovative privatepublic engagement  years of monopoly transformed  points of presence pops served policy contributions commissioner contributions are shown in the context of the i framework  ingredient i framework of information infrastructure power software payload human environment hardware network policy affiliations selected contributions   the red thread my fortunate life in telecommunications publication “brian thompson is a pioneer of the market based telecom revolution” richard e cavanagh fmr ceo the conference board inc fmr executive dean  harvard kennedy school home teacher student writer researcher learner  limestone under construction h brian thompson under construction homelimestoneosucontactcurriculum vita under construction oklahoma state welcome all copyright  h brian thompson all rights reserved view on mobile bio  the red thread home bio tribute endorsements news  events how to buy bio the red thread  my fortunate life in telecommunications h brian thompson is executive chairman of gtt the premier cloud network provider to the world powered by its global ethernet and ip backbone gtt operates the most interconnected network on the globe from its headquarters in the washington dc metro region and offices in chicago denver london frankfurt milan and cagliari italy thompson continues to head his own private equity investment and advisory firm universal telecommunications inc in vienna virginia focused on both startup companies and consolidations taking place in the informationtelecommunications business areas both domestically and internationally uti has played a key role in the formation andor management of companies such as neustar comsat international gtt itown communications and the fiberutilities group as a veteran senior executive of the telecommunication industry thompson has been instrumental in impacting the rise of competitive telecommunications both in the us and abroad from december  to june  thompson was chairman of comsat international inc ci one of the largest independent telecommunications operators serving all of latin america he also served as chairman and chief executive officer of global telesystems group inc from march  through september of  thompson was chairman and ceo of lci international he joined lci in  and with his team led the turnaround of the company and its emergence as one of the fastest growing telecommunications companies in the us subsequent to the merger of lci with qwest communications international inc in june  thompson became vice chairman of the board for qwest until his resignation in december  thompson previously served as executive vice president of mci communications corporation from  to  with responsibility for the company’s eight operating divisions including mci international during his  years with mci as a senior executive he contributed greatly to that company’s growth from  million to  billion in revenue and to the internationalization of the company prior to mci thompson was a management consultant with the washington dc offices of mckinsey  company for nine years where he specialized in the management of telecommunications and technology enterprises he currently serves as a director of axcelis technologies inc pendrell corporation penske automotive group and sonus networks inc and formerly served on the boards of arraycomm bell canada international inc comcast uk cable partners limited dyncorp williams communications group inc and golden books he serves as a member of the irish prime minister’s irelandamerica economic advisory board and is a member of the board of trustees of the lab school of washington  baltimore lab he is a former chairman of the us competitive telecommunications association comptel and also served on the university of massachusetts chancellor’s executive committee as a trustee of capitol college in laurel md and trustee of the st stephens and st agnes school foundation in alexandria va thompson served as the cochairman for the americas and on the executive committee of the global information infrastructure commission a multinational organization launched in brussels in  to chart the role of the private sector in the developing global information and telecommunications infrastructure for ireland’s department of public enterprise mr thompson served as chairman of both the advisory committee for telecommunications and more recently the advisory committee on infocoms for the period januarymarch  he served as chairman of telecom eireann ireland’s incumbent telephone company thompson spent four years in the us navy as a divingdemolition officer in the eod explosive ordnance disposal branch from 666 and worked for the kendall company monsanto and celenese in chemical engineering research before completing graduate school and entering the business world thompson received his mba from harvard’s graduate school of business 6 and holds an undergraduate degree in chemical engineering from the university of massachusetts 6 “read this book learn from brians experience at 